===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|j}}: Variant form of {{och-l|*枼}} (the original form of {{och-l|葉|leaf|id=2}}) with the tree removed.

''{{w|Shuowen}}'' interprets it as {{och-l|*十}} triplicated: thirty [[year]]s make one [[generation]] (thirty times twelve months gives 360 months).

===Etymology===
{{och-l|世}} is derived from iterative devoicing of {{och-l|葉|leaf|id=2}} + *''-s'' suffix, meaning successive foliages of a tree > generations. Compare {{cog|bo|ལོ་མ||leaf}}, Western {{cog|bo|ལོབ་མ||leaf}} and {{cog|bo|ལོ||year}}.

